  • Method Details

    • onInitiation

      public void onInitiation(GameEngine gameEngine)
      A method to control the behaviour of an Encounter when initially traversed to. If an onInitiationBehaviour exists then this is executed and the player can continue to interact with the encounter.
      Parameters:
      gameEngine - The current instance of the GameEngine is required so that dependencies such as the current encounter and player can be referenced.

    • isOnInitiationUseable

      public boolean isOnInitiationUseable()
      Returns:
      Returns true in the event that there is an on-use behavior set that can execute when the onUse() method is called.

    • setOnInitiationBehaviour

      public void setOnInitiationBehaviour(Useable onInitiationBehaviour)
      Parameters:
      onInitiationBehaviour - Intended to use a lambda to allow developers to create custom behaviours when an encounter is first traversed to. Example of a lambda created using the generic Useable interface: Useable onUseInitiation = (gameEngine) -> { var player = gameEngine.getPlayer(); player.subtractFromCurrentHealth(6); gameEngine.printMessage("On entering the encounter you suffered 6 damage " + "from a rusty doornail!"); };

    • getOnInitiationBehaviour

    • save

      public void save(String path) throws IOException
      Serialises to a local path. The file type extension is '.ser'.
      Parameters:
      path - The location that the .ser file will be saved to, along with the file name. Example: encounter.save("src/fileName");
      Throws:
      IOException - Arises if the file path cannot be serialised to.
      InvalidPathException - Arises if the path contains characters other than the English alphabet, underscores, and forward slashes.

    • save

      public void save(String path, String fileExtension) throws IOException
      Serialises to a local path. The file type extension is decided by the developer.
      Parameters:
      path - The location that the .ser file will be saved to, along with the file name. Example: encounter.save("src/fileName", "sav");
      fileExtension - The file type extension the developer wishes to save the file as.
      Throws:
      IOException - Arises if the file path cannot be serialised to.
      InvalidPathException - Arises if the path contains characters other than the English alphabet, underscores, and forward slashes.

    • load

      public static Encounter load(String path) throws IOException, ClassNotFoundException
      Serialises to a local path. The file type extension is only required when the extension is something other than '.ser'.
      Parameters:
      path - The location that the file is located at. This can either be with or without the file extension. Examples: var combatEncounter = (CombatEncounter) Encounter.load("src/fileNameWithSavExtension.sav"); or var nonCombatEncounter = (NonCombatEncounter) Encounter.load("src/fileNameWithSerExtension");
      Throws:
      IOException - Arises if the file path cannot be serialised to.
      ClassNotFoundException - Arises if the file cannot be deserialised to this class. underscores, and forward slashes.
